{{efn
| name = gun nomenclature
| In Imperial German Navy gun nomenclature, "SK" (Schnelladekanone) denotes that the gun is quick firing, while the L/50 denotes the length of the gun. In this case, the L/50 gun is 50 [[Caliber (artillery)|caliber]], meaning that the gun is 50 times as long as its diameter.
}}

